.TH "scsi_add_host_with_dma" 9 "scsi_add_host_with_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_add_host_with_dma \- add a scsi host with dma device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_add_host_with_dma
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device *dma_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shost" 12
scsi host pointer to add
.IP "dev" 12
a struct device of type scsi class
.IP "dma_dev" 12
dma device for the host
.SH "NOTE"
You rarely need to worry about this unless you're in a
virtualised host environments, so use the simpler \fBscsi_add_host\fP
function instead.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return value: 
0 on success / != 0 for error
